info.name: Dungeon Speeders
info.attribution:
How to use the room:
Take a seat in the upper right corner. After everyone is seated, press the "reset" button under the timer and choose your settings. The "play" button starts the round and places the new target location onto the map. 
If you find a path to the target, take the corresponding number from the sorted array to the left and place it into the square next to your name. This will start the timer for the other players. 
You can hover over the rectangular hero pieces on the right to have a detailed description of each hero's power. The round pieces on the map only show the symbol of its power. 
The grid on the right can be used to help you plan and keep track of the number of turns for each hero, especially when moving multiple heroes in one turn.
The button on the left border of the room expands a view of the progress of other players.

info.description: Players compete to be the first to have one of their 8 tokens reach the target using the fewest possible moves and the special powers of each token. Once one playerâ€™s token reaches the target, that token is collected and no longer available for that player to use. First player to collect 6 tokens wins.

fighterMarker.hoverNote: The Fighter may move one space orthogonally: left, right, up, or down. Her ability counts as a separate move.

mageMarker.hoverNote: The Mage can teleport from anywhere directly to any Mage symbol. After she teleports, she stops. Teleporting counts as a move.

rangerMarker.hoverNote: The Ranger wraps around the dungeon edges. Use the letters on the edges as guides. When he uses his ability to go off the edge of the map, he'll reappear on the opposite side of the map at the same letter, and will continue moving in the direction he was moving until he is stopped by a Hero or a wall. His ability does not count as an additional move.

barbarianMarker.hoverNote: The Barbarian may pass through any wall. After passing through a wall, the Barbarian continues in the direction he was moving and only stops when he hits another wall, another hero, or a dungeon edge. This ability does not count as an additional move.

clericMarker.hoverNote: The Cleric may move one space diagonally. He may move past a wall, but not through it (where two walls join to make a corner). He may move past a Hero or 'between' Heroes. His ability counts as an additional move.

bardMarker.hoverNote: The Bard may use the ability of any Hero who is not yet in your party. She may use any single ability once per round, and may never use more than one power per round.

rogueMarker.hoverNote: The Rogue jumps three spaces (neither more nor less) orthogonally: left, right, up, or down. He jumps over any walls and Heros on those two spaces. The space he lands on cannot have a Hero on it. This ability counts as a separate move.

alchemistMarker.hoverNote: The Alchemist may stop one space short of any wall, Hero, or dungeon edge. Her ability does not count as an additional move.
